Our aims were:
to analyze the association between sensitization to single hazelnut allergens and clinical symptom severity;
to evaluate their ability to discriminate between mild and severe hazelnut allergy.

Conclusions: Thus, at the absence of breast milk, infants with FA manifestations are expedient to feed with the following mixtures:
with complete protein hydrolysis (Alfare);
acidophilic (Acidophilic NAN);
alactic (NAN Lactose free);
soy-bean (NAN Soy).
